reviews.review_text: Easy 4.5...Good  Stuff All Around Another one of those sources and shows that really should be at about 4 1/2 stars.  4 for the performance, which is yet another example of the great run that was Fall 79.  First Set smokes and the Second kicks it up a notch.  Band is in the groove and doesn't waste a single note.  Now the sound I'd have to give 5 stars.  Clear and crispy.  Phil is upfront and center, driving the train with great sound and depth.  Good work on this one.  Without a doubt worth a listen.

Top of the List! This is one of my all time favs! where to start? The mexacali is nice into a blackbird tease. But the Shakedown into Sampson then hightime is outstanding! But the estimated into eyes is unbelievable! Then a nice black peter.I may have to say one of the better ones! I would love to hear a challange jdgatorz@yahoo.com.
What a... Great great show! I'm totally digging the estimated prophet to eyes. Stellar performace, great sound quality, greatest band. Thank you Thank you for the grateful dead!

This show thumps Standout versions of BE Women, LL Rain. Jerry really starts to let go with the fast driven noodling during
Samson and Eyes, which is stellar.

Peace
Great '79 Show The first set was bit hit and miss for me but the pre-drum second set run is excellent with a super-fast Eyes common to the era. Jerry just rips it.
Yes  great show This is great
I smell smoke... What's not to like, Outstanding! Thanks again Charlie
fun night loaded up Mr evens Mr dugan Mr raketich , Mr Roror and left sharon Pa a Good time was had by all, part of a Pittsburg , Buffalo Run !Great music

The Greatful Dead I had a ticket to post.mispelled? yes..

This performance was "The Greatful Dead"

I believe that is all I need to say

Thnx again to the one and only Charlie Miller! Great example of Famous Fall ‘79 on display. Brent getting in there and playing his own sound, the boys rocking hard and also putting out some smooth soft ballads .... thank you cleaveland! Man, ‘79 was truly something. Glad to have good sound quality to prove the naysayers that the Dead did bring it! RIP Jerry. Miss u daily!
